message: Bose doesn't have good mids, so I'm not looking there.

I'm pretty happy with my klipsch image s4.  Although they don't stay in to well when running,  but they are fine of desk work though.  Mine are about 1.5~ years old i think, still holding up well.

I recommend Creative Aurvana http://us.store.creative.com/Creative-Aurvana-InEar-Earphones/M/B000I13TBS.htm or creative ep-630 http://us.store.creative.com/category/55620695201/1/EP630.htm
Sennheiser is my favourite - CX300, 400 or 500, but the web is full of heavily discounted fakes. Always read user comments and avoid retailers that allow third parties to sell under their name.
Check out jays. Their a jays lone is top notch and well received by reveiewers
I'm using Etymotics ER-6i.. Very clear, great isolation. Bass is present but not it's strongest point.
+1 Klipsch IMAGE S4

I agree with PhotoPanda that the Etymotics are great. I used to have a pair of the ER-6, but then I 'upgraded' to the MC-3 <http://www.etymotic.com/ephp/mc3.html> so I could use the in-line mic on my iPhone.
i usually go with skullcandy.. but ive been using some cheap ones i got from fye.. but nerdist has a deal on this website tweakedaudio.com/nerdist
I have the smart buds from Zagg.com. Good quality nod only $50.

I have some nice Sony earbuds that I purchased at BestBuy for less then fifty dollars. They are basic, but work beautifully. I don't know how serious you are about headphones, but I personally prefer earbuds.
I ended up going with Woodees IESW100L BLUES, and I'm pleased with the purchase. I wrote a review here: http://wp.me/pkhbD-1mp
Thank you to everyone who took time to reply.
For in ear, the Shure SE210.

Recently bought the Phonak Audeo PFE 022 to replace my broken Shure SE530's, I love them very comfy with decent sound, comes with a mic and only cost £90. I found them to be slightly better than the Klispch Image S4 in sound quality and seem to look more durable.
I have some really nice Sony headphones. I can reccomend their head phones. I don't however remember their name, nor do I have their package anymore.
Shure all the way.

I've tried a bunch of the in-ears that have iPhone controls (Shure, Klipsch, V-MODA, Beats) but my favorite is the Beats. The sound is comparable to the others in the same price range but the flat cable is really awesome because it doesn't tangle easily. http://www.amazon.com/Beats-Tour-Mobile-Control-Headphones/dp/B002EL4RI4
